    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>Royal Observatory Greenwich</placeName>
                        <date>November 30 1849</date>
                        <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>I received at Cambridge your note of the 24th. I have since returned and have attended Mr. Ransome's funeral, and have returned again.</p>
                        <p>I do not think of subscribing to Mr. G. Ransome's portrait because such things are not in my way, I can find better methods of showing my respect.</p>
                        <p>Your conjectural equation A. B. G. = G. B. A. is exceedingly plausible, and I think it likely that many reasons might be addressed for showing that it is a good approximation.</p>
                        <p>With best regards to Mrs Henslow I am, my dear Sir,</p>
                        <p>Yours very truly</p>
                        <p>G. B. Airy</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
